column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "6D03EFED4C167128A8D70E945FE0F9B3", "These boots of cloth wrapped and laced in hide, provide protection and warmth for the feet.\nThere are many dangers in the Exiled Lands and the small scorpions, spiders and snakes that can strike without warning are reason enough to keep legs and feet well covered.\nCreated from basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this armor bears no cultural markings or identifiers of any type.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FE66A95049B87847500F55B092CD6686", "A mask worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "EDF908824E5852DDF683268DD6422BA4", "The dispassionate features of the serpent have been modeled and refined in this mask. It distorts the features of the wearer and brings them closer to the cold beauty of the serpents so beloved of their god.\nUsed primarily in rituals within the temple of Set, this mask nevertheless offers a certain level of protection for the face of the wearer.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "BB61A7234D27E91B625B009405D75B50", "A choker worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "50FDB53040B0622F8336FB802EDA6988", "Crafted from the finest golds, this garment is light and supple. It molds pleasingly to the form and accentuates the chest. The mysteries of Set are not all blood and death - the ritual that depicts the coupling of Set with his mistress, Derkheto, has been described by Mitrean scholars as \"a blasphemous orgy of wine and blood.\" Though they always take the opportunity to vist any temple of Derkheto during such rites. For the purposes of research, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "8505FEB4452C69A2276FD1B1EB3311EA", "A shendyt worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "BB8C05CA4EBD99C8F76F25907BA9716B", "Woven silk edged with golden trim has been used to shape this ornamental shendyt. Worn by devotees of Set during their rituals, these shendyts are often stained in the blood of sacrifice.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C69C0F794BF681EF427BC88FBB2C9F33", "A pair of sandals worn by devotees of Set")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "77D6A9F1409F27595A912DA91AD937D5", "These ceremonial sandals were not designed for the harsh environment of the desert, but rather the stone floors of the temple. Runnng in sand wearing these is an uncomfortable experience and fighting in them is almost impossible due to poor balance.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "17D92DAA490AE8F521EEB6B98854C5F3", "A ritual mask used by Yoggite shamans to see the dead")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "74F81D9144126265C4376292382DD1D3", "Carved into solid wood and decorated with intricate symbols, the watcher mask is said to remove the veil between the wearer and the spiritual world where Yog dwells.
Darfari slaves, captured and carried into the Hyborian kingdoms do not have shamans of their own, and are forced to practise a perverted version of their religion. They have long since lost the art of creating masks such as these.
But in the southern deserts, Darfari shamans practise a purer version of the religion. Through the aid of these masks they can see the dead and, it is rumored, manifestations of Yog himself.

This mask offers some protection from both weapons and the elements.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "658144CD47E06A35EA670BA0A11192A8", "An ornate necklace of teeth over human skin")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "007CF00047913F660061C48D291734BE", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
This chestpiece is soft and supple, which allows for great flexibility. The teeth used in the necklace appear to be crocodile teeth, taken from the great beasts that roam the Exiled Lands.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "53F0EB144D4113C3D5F12ABA77B226BD", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These bracers are the color of blood and made of a soft leather wrapped with cloth. A close look reveals human molars dangling from the bindings on the gauntlets.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "C0B20BC94C6F0917B425B3A175D2E8BA", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These skirt is simple and adorned with a belt of small beads and human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "13360A3E421E0FB1B2FF5FB3175AC461", "It is no secret that Darfari consume the flesh of the dead but the horrible reality of the Exiled Lands has forced them to perform other perverted acts. This includes stripping the skin from their victims to create a soft leather that can be used for crafting armor.
These leather wraps, generously called greaves, are supple leather adorned with human bones and teeth.

Light armor provides the most flexibility and range of movement in combat, but at the cost of significant protection in battle.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "B2C6189046D55DB721EAC3BCFB30FE5D", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThis tunic reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "A5D806DD4E140FA4079CE8AA7EEF8922", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese gloves reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "2AFA4FE04558DB14DDAE9D826338E899", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese breeches reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "69E4B6E2464176058CA1EC9AF402AA19", "Followers of Mitra commit to a life of simplicty and dignity. They prefer knowledge to ritual and the calm of meditation to the storm of battle.\nThese shoes reflects the simple principles of the Mitraen devout.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "11C7B17B4ADD4ACA296F83BD30B467C3", "A patchwork vest of leather, rope and cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "98481D4C4159C063820F0F8BA884EBF7", "One of the skills that sailors carry with them from port to port is the ability to mend almost any piece of cloth with a needle. Sailors repair their own sails and their clothes turning them overtime into a patchwork of sailcloth, rope a bit of scrap leather. This garment, favored bt eh sailors of the Black Hand looks as though it has been mended so many times that none of the original material is left. Still due to the age of the garment and the many layers it exhibits more durability than it\'s frail appearance would indicate. \nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "7DFA511A47CC599EB16728BCE7779715", "A heavily stitched pair of leather pants")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "64A8EB3F4F64CC5939F5478FEFEB8FD6", "The pirates of the Black Hand are the most dangerous kind of pirates - shipless, aimless and destitute. They search desperately for a way to leave the Exiled Lands and they form strange alliances and quirky plans to help them achieve that goal. So far, nothing has come to fruition.\nThese trousers are a reflection of their attitude, a patchwork of sloppy stitching and flung together pieces. Like the Black Hand, however, it seems to work.\nOffering significantly more protection than light armor, this medium armor incorporates many elements that balance protection and agility. This middle of the road approach brings compromises of its own because this armor is neither as strong as heavy armor, nor as flexible as light armor.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "0783E7D842571FCC8A273FAED0130603", "XX_Desert_Dogs_Helmet")
NSLOCTEXT("", "B24A30F2465D420924AC7885A3067798", "XX_Desert_Dogs_Chestpiece")
NSLOCTEXT("", "9A330DBB4E79D5A9CB29E5B6D8611C6F", "XX_Desert_Dogs_Gauntlets")
NSLOCTEXT("", "BC9336DE4B38436E43FE06A405A4C47C", "XX_Desert_Dogs_Tasset")
NSLOCTEXT("", "EA8D12C9435D250750B596B6F21DD136", "XX_Desert_Dogs_Boots")

NSLOCTEXT("", "A8B91B0B478B302E58F55586E18DA9DB", "Stygian traditions of healing hold that the aloe plant contains many desirable properties. In Luxur, the aloe is harvested for use in the temples of Derkheto to cleanse blemishes from the skin of the priestesses. It is often used to sooth oozing wounds and those who ingest it claim that they feel a burst of wellbeing. Whether these effects are of the body or the mind is irrelevant - ingesting aloe extract seems to give the imbiber a regenerative health effect.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C95DA79441C6FBFFE1EDA7A1DD0A3C3E", "A brilliant purple potion that cures everything")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "5FE9FC0A40E58D3448B6188567B9CE00", "Extracted from the venom of various poisonous snakes, this violet potion seems to purge the system of all natural negative effects upon use. Commonly used by street performers in Vendhya to shrug off the effects of cobra bites, more fools have died trying to harvest the ingredients for the cure-all than would have died if the cure-all did not exist at all.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "53A6D26646EF6E3E4F1B9AB62F06A664", "A potion that causes hallucinations and visions")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "D0F399174E05A5C0D16C19AD1AA37A40", "The yellow lotus is used by sorcerers to provide visions and trances, with a strong hallucinogenic effect. It is said that those who survive the visions are given a deeper insight into the world, able to communicate with the inner world in a way that rewrites their very physique. In reality, the effect of the potion blanks the mind, freeing one to focus on a new set of skills at the cost of forgetting all previous abilities and skills.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "318147144254013B071067BCC0B5C3A9", "A poison that can be applied to daggers")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "D6A1727A4FC801CCA04FD4A8E8646AD3", "The toxin gland of the Sand Reapers is difficult to obtain due to the ferocious nature of the creatures. When properly prepared, it becomes a poison that can be applied to certain weapons, such as daggers, and then used to debilitate foes. In Vendhya, assassins often use poison to kill their targets - the current king has weathered no less than five attempts on his life thus far, though the five skulls bleaching on the Tower of the Kites are evidence of their failure.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "394A40A54C8D657813E82BBBAA1E25DA", "XX_Demon\'s Bane")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "DFACD11B477E275AB35695ADA22E85F6", "Flesh that has been ritually purified")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "5F8AFA93409A9A9A9AA6F185C79C46E8", "Devotees of Yog have purified this flesh in the firepits of sacrifice. It can be eaten to gain the favour of Yog.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "0B418E9F44510821B3ABCC8F7B4057E1", "A dish purported to be blessed by the gods")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "8F9681E64D0C552ED4B38EBF8AE1B8EA", "Worshippers of Mitra often bring sacrifices of fruit or grain to lay upon his altar, in return for his blessing. And occasionally his blessing is very formidable indeed, taking the form of Ambrosia. This bizarre substance, considered a food of the gods, has healing properties that the Priests of Mitra use to bring strength and vitality to the poor. How it is made is pure conjecture, as it seems to congeal within empty vessels left out on the altar with no physical intervention from priest or penitent.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "6F427B8C452FA26C2E0A70B4951D52D3", "Set commands that his followers revere serpents above all creatures, even requiring that his devotees allow themselves to be devoured by the giant temple snakes if the creatures so desire. This reverence means that many priests are bitten by the venemous serpents that roam the stone temples. Rather than simply accept their fate at the hands of a petulant snake, the priests often keep a supply of this antidote handy. Created during the rituals of sacrifice from the hearts of humans, it is a literal trade of a life for a life and Set does not seem to hold any grudges against followers who spare themselves in this manner.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "A9068FA1481ECFBC258767969E516EE1", "Flinthead Bolts")
NSLOCTEXT("", "4E1ADCED4C557724FA19ACBCBCD171FD", "Ironhead Bolts")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "B4B427E9438206105C1DF99413888B8F", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Set")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "EA0573E4460A81A7ADF893BB895383AF", "<span style="italic">Some gods are strong to harm, others, to aid; at least so say their priests.</>
Queen of the Black Coast
Learning true names is a study that sorcerers use to contact the demons of the Outer Void. Such sorcerers have volumes full of the names of their familiars and allies.
The true name of a god, however, burns brightly in the mind when spoken, then flares and fades into nothingness. Once spoken, such a name is forgotten immediately.
This name then, carved in stone, is a priceless gift. For a short period, the gaze of a god will be upon the speaker and they will be lifted to heights of power undreamed of. But men were not built to live as gods, so the power is fleeting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "9BF658E94FE15D347EFE408FB6827455", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "028AE8D3417F71C8F9E552AB5176BE4F", "<span style="italic">Some gods are strong to harm, others, to aid; at least so say their priests.</>
Queen of the Black Coast
Learning true names is a study that sorcerers use to contact the demons of the Outer Void. Such sorcerers have volumes full of the names of their familiars and allies.

This name then, carved in stone, is a priceless gift. For a short period, the gaze of a god will be upon the speaker and they will be lifted to heights of power undreamed of. But men were not built to live as gods, so the power is fleeting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C06F3E034E4C19155E1F65BE4AD00198", "Use to invoke the Avatar of Mitra")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "845C82D6437B78426A179FB770553636", "<span style="italic">Some gods are strong to harm, others, to aid; at least so say their priests.</>
Queen of the Black Coast
Learning true names is a study that sorcerers use to contact the demons of the Outer Void. Such sorcerers have volumes full of the names of their familiars and allies.
The true name of a god, however, burns brightly in the mind when spoken, then flares and fades into nothingness. Once spoken, such a name is forgotten immediately.
This name then, carved in stone, is a priceless gift. For a short period, the gaze of a god will be upon the speaker and they will be lifted to heights of power undreamed of. But men were not built to live as gods, so the power is fleeting.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "CF3BB3A2444BA052A995A3AD96E5ED60", "A spiritual residue left on religious altars")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "CD30932F45A03732A6259484A60DC4B3", "Over time, a place that is used for religious ceremonies takes on a certain significance. Not simply in the minds of the followers of that religion, but also in others who pass through an area.\nIn the oldest groves and shrines of the world, the presence of those ancient, gloomy gods can still be felt. In the shining altars of Mitra or the bloody slabs of Set, the manifestation of this spiritual presence is palpable.\nWhen a shrine is defiled, this effect leeches slowly away, but if the defilers are of an opposing religion, they actually absorb the power that they have stolen. Thus altars are a precious commodity in the Exiled Lands and worship brings great bounties to those who pursue it.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "37E150054827C3D839D4ADB5EC34CFDB", "Imp Idol Eye")

NSLOCTEXT("", "F7394E8D49ADCC16156231AFF5A1480B", "Few of the inhabitants of the Exiled Lands are lucky enough to sleep in a bed at night. Some disdain the comfort of a full bed, imagining that the softness of the mattress will cause a softening of their bodies and minds.\nBut some see the bed as a place of lovemaking, sleeping and dreaming. They consider it an important part of civilization and sneer at those who sleep on the ground as uncouth savages.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E3F425904485D042C748D984262FC46B", "A folding bed that takes up little space")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "FEAD5AFE4D041C9C277C72AD9A7F5FFD", "This bed made of leather stretched over a folding frame, take up less space than a conventional bed.\nCommonly used in barracks, cheap inns and mercenary headquarters, this bed is valued mostly for its ability to be stacked and stored whenever it isn?t being used.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "2A96BBF842A1C88E8429028A05A23910", "A low divan made in the Stygian style")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "2704524E4039979E082C438C0080A410", "Both couch and bed, the divan probably originated in Vendhya or Turan, but it rapidly became popular in the kingdom of Stygia. The most elaborate of divans are made of silk and gold inlaid ebony, but they can also be made from simple materials.\nStygian nobles are often portrayed as indolent and decadent and imagery of them lounging on divans, eating and drinking, has contributed to this portrayal. In practicality, during the hottest hours of the day all Stygians retire to their houses for leisure time and these rumors are probably spread by foreign merchants frustrated with a culture that doesn?t follow their schedule.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bed will set it as your spawn point until it is destroyed.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FFEA92E84825349C42CEAFB196618CEB", "A rawhide bedroll for sleeping on the ground.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "8ED030B84F8578E47A75B3A00D5C479D", "Roughly sewn together from the hides of animals, this bedroll offers warmth and some small protection from sharp rocks and twigs on the grounds.\nThe price, of course, is the sharp smell of untreated leather and the occasional unwanted attentions of passing animals.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bedroll will set it as your spawn point temporarily, until you have died once.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "4C5B914248BB2A05A8F27E84C00B313D", "A mattress of leaves, twigs and grass.")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "B223FDA74E41D55100FE118E0E522BE7", "A hastily gathered bundle of fibers stripped from the plants and vegetation that dot the Exiled Lands, this bedroll offers very little in the way warmth or protection.\nIt?s probably better than lying on the hard ground though. Slightly.\nWhen somebody dies in the Exiled Lands, they awaken in the last place that they slept, unaware of how or why they got there. Using a bedroll will set it as your spawn point temporarily, until you have died once.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FD37ED2D474B9F845E171AAB4D4F2821", "A simple tent that offers protection against sandstorms")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "DE83901041A156698AC36EB217C2901F", "The Zuagir, a tribe of shemite nomads who roam the sands from Zamora to Zamboula, created these tents as a rather novel way to ride out the sandstorms which sweep the deserts of Hyboria.
Made of woven camel-hair, these tents are deployed quickly and with little fuss and are actually quite a comfortable place to ride out a sandstorm.
Sandstorms in the Exiled Lands contain more than just wind-blown sand and flying fragments. There are darker terrors against which woven camelhair may not prove particularly effective.
Once a tent is placed, hiding inside is as simple as using it.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "AE081C114641F4C1678ABE89396B1217", "A well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "F140FE0F498EB9F602D1FEA6171EF9D8", "Made from rough stones and wood, this well manages to capture a small amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C1C9701E43CE43B8BDEA97A3BFE76861", "A large well that fills slowly over time")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "23649877463FE02C417EBD9E29793A76", "Made from well-fitted, tight stonework, this well captures a generous amount of water.\nWater is an essential element for survival and this is doubly the case in the desert environments of the Exiled Lands. Any permanent settlement near water will inevitable be contested by others who also seek access to this life affirming resource.\nThe convenience of a well allows building in areas that would otherwise be unsustainable. Wells fill with water over time and can be used to quench thirst, replenish waterskins and perform the dozens of other activities that require the presence of water.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C63641094DB2ABBBCBEBB7868C3DDF73", "A training dummy for practising combat techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "21D8028649E0D3DC6CE23EBDC107993C", "Made of stuffed straw and rough cloth, this dummy is a stand in for the horrendous creatures of the Exiled Lands.\nThe ability to guage hit locations from the markings on the dummy is a great way for warriors to increase their abilities.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "4D92A793420547B29E5A848DF587FF20", "A target for refining ranged techniques")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "364C95BB4D4715E3651818AC0B8D2A0D", "Bows require a lifetime of discipline to master and those who do not practise regularly will find themselves losing the edge.\nThis target provides a perfect opportunity to practise with bows, crossbows and thrown weapons without the inevitable conflict that comes from shooting somebody full of arrows.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "DE00080A42ADEDC52E65CAB7E8BE8D2D", "This spike can be decorated with various skulls")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "DF26772B4609A300BB5967ABE74D43BE", "This sharpened wooden spike, once placed, waits patiently for something to be impaled upon it.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "C390F7614EB973B8C58DE29318A15CB4", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden rectangle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "4F7D2CFF412204B8875309A58FE8CD67", "Tables vary in shape and size, materials and decoration based on the culture and craftsmanship of their maker.\nThis one is a wooden circle.\nThe artisan was probably hoping to decorate the table with dozens of interesting objects and thereby distract from the lack of imagination in the creation of the table itself.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "CBBA26AD4A92C604905F1BA9D7B8455F", "These makeshift bundles of sharpened wooden stakes are usually placed around mercenary camps and other temporary fortifications.\nNo sane soldier wants to charge an enemy who has ringed their camp with barricades such as these.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FC62B7D24CB0E446A58DEA960A239DEF", "A barricade of high sharpened stakes")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "D13FBF3C47EDDC8CFB2BD380F7C96273", "Designed as a foil to cavalry charges, the stakes on these barricades were originally about chest high to a horse. Over time it was discovered that the closer the spikes were to eye height on a horse, the less chance that the beast could be coerced into charging them.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "B2BFEC83491C5E03ACFBA6BFF8135CDA", "Sometimes after a day of killing and slaying, all an Exile wants to do is sit down and relax.\nStools are often used as makeshift weapons in tavern brawls across Hyboria, usually hurled at an opponent in between curses.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "4CE4D5E14E3F87CC304E32ADC0CDE06D", "Useful for sitting and hurling at enemies.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "1E6338BE47DA8B31A0B334BA980FD931", "Crafted by weaving thin bands of hard wood into a strong yet pliable surface, this stool is comfortable to sit on and very lightweight.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "E14EDFBA47649D1872675DBD711A4B21", "Commonly found only in the houses of the wealthy or noble, chairs with armrests and backs are considered a mark of refinement.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "A378B7D44F611480332BD980CEA920AE", "Benches like this are common in the taverns and alehouses of the world. ")

NSLOCTEXT("", "CD68D68142B230840B8E62A0EA68C2EE", "Unlike other chairs, a throne gives the one who sits in it authority above and beyond that of an ordinary man.\nBattles have always been fought for this kind of power, and they always will be.\nSitting on a throne of any kind will increase confidence and prowess for a period.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "70A4DFC744886560E41A9182FD496965", "In the Western kingdoms of Aquilonia and Nemedia, the practise of using wooden signs to provide warning and information for travellers and merchants has been established for centuries.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "53A9F20547FFE51F6FBB9D95628756D5", "Designed to be placed on walls and provide information about the location, these signs are a mark of civilization beyond what most people would expect to find in the Exiled Lands.\nOnce a signpost is placed, it can be used to write a custom message for any travellers to read.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "C6CEA6D44F497C39FCB42CBD67AF66E7", "A scroll made from flattened reed stalks")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "DD1F332B43C4FAD8FBCF9DB8A32F3C68", "Made from the pith of flattened reeds, papyrus scrolls are commonly used in Stygia for holding the words of sacred texts.\nThe material used is too brittle to be very good for the creation of long-form texts, but for simple messages a papyrus scroll is cheap and easy to produce.\nThis scroll can be filled in, and then shared with others. If they can read, of course. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "F399819D4A760CCEE3634AA1B5DD033E", "A tall torch that can be placed in the ground")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "08F84D0647A09F2369132CBAD3CD9F2C", "A large torch that can be placed in the ground to create light in an area. Some use these as beacons, to light their way home on the darkest of nights.\nIn the Exiled Lands, the torches of the Darfari Cannibals are prominent in the darkness. In their camps, the cannibals dance madly to the throbbing of skin-covered drums and their frenzy amongst the flickering light of torch and cookfire seems oddly appropriate.\nThese torches can be lit and unlit without fuel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "6C859D754A3DBCA9B99AE7BE4C293165", "An ornate brazier made in the Stygian fashion")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "A6D251644A4D169351695C92D1B4A06F", "This small brazier, made of bronze worked into the shape of a serpent, is commonly found in Stygian temples of Set. \nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon. ")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "80DF25F04DF5232A3A954AABB83612BA", "An iron bracketed torch that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "1AFAC6A947634559A16015823B5C9BD4", "Defending a fortification during a night assault is made infinitely simpler by the ability to see where the enemy is coming from.\nAttaching torches to the walls of a building can free hands to grip a blade or pike and cast a light upon the activities of enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "8DC676724E6357BF72378BAF9CD4A8C3", "An iron-sheathed lantern that can be attached to a wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "3E293D4242C7732D7925A7AFF6F7EB1C", "This ornate lantern bears patterning that seems to indicate that it is of Turanian origin. It is well known that the rich quarter of Agrapur has street lanterns placed at regular intervals to discourage thieves.\nLanterns have a steadier light than torches, and they remain lit for longer. However, the soft glow of a lantern fails to evoke the same primal urges as the naked flame.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "B44F20434CB7E0E831DE6A86DEF2F5F3", "The melted, half-used stub of a candle")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "57028CBF4BCB3FD9A86602938114EF85", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nMade from beeswax shaped around a treated wick, this candle has been used extensively in the past.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "A6717A04499B112E4AD67A8208975DF3", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nWhite candles are often burned in the temples of Mitra representing the purity of thought and knowledge that Mitra brings to his followers.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "E002031B4966F08980A73FA6A0FB50FE", "Used primarily indoors, candles are the cheapest light source available. In royal castles, great candelabras with hundreds of candles light great ballrooms and throne rooms, while in the huts of peasants a single candle burns in the night to illuminate those simple tasks that are performed once the sun has dropped below the horizon.\nBlack candles are sought after by sorcerers for use in their rituals. The vilest of men purportedly create candles from the blood of demons for communicating with presences that circle in the Outer Void.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "429A317D48491FABDE4A2E9739C05F1C", "An odd gem that glows when rubbed")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "9953C08045BF43FCDB14B792F224EC3D", "<span style=\"italic\">\'They are jewels, fused with radium. You rub them with your thumb to make them glow, and rub them again, the opposite way, to extinguish them.\'</>\nXuthal of the Dusk\nThe product of a science long vanished in the ancient past, these gems seem to glow indefinitely when activated. There is a cost, however, as those who use the Radium Gems seem to slowly lose their grip on sanity, whispering to themselves of green stoned cities and the nameless horrors that stalk them.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "03BE027C44C7E723D57AD5B37085876A", "A patterned tapestry in earthen colors")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "AD0061BE452CDEA9E7BD0F84ED0CEFD2", "Tapestries such as this travel the Lotus road between Khitai and the Kingdoms of the West daily. Woven of plant fibers or silk, they vary in quality and quantity based entirely on the skill of the weaver and the materials used. \nThat these can be made in the Exiled Lands, without a loom, is impressive.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "B2B2BB2D44BA94459B5F01837ECB6235", "A length of chain that can be attached to the wall")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "87E9634145334B0C0A54C68715985AD5", "Chains have been the preferred choice of ornamentation for despots and tyrants for thousands of years. Many a diplomat has made less-than-favorable bargains under the intimidation of cold steel.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E6AA08564A70F6A3E514FEBF2862E4FC", "A small awning of orange cloth")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "4A2A756A40CCD53C0AFC04A3106FB436", "Among the great bazaars of Khemi, merchants use awnings such as this to protect their wares from the harsh Stygian sun.\nBy their nature, these awnings are made to be taken up and down quickly. They are not particularly robust, but they do offer shade when needed.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "7C3BD2E04600663586C8468FDF78C317", "Woven of coarse fibers, this carpet is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "2A53D89248D30F2938F02AA19287EE52", "In the gloomy hills of Cimmeria and the snow capped ranges of Vanaheim and Asgard, animal hides and furs are considered a necessity. Hide rugs are a common floor ornament considered doubly practical if the fur is left attached.\nThey also have a distinctive fragrance.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "760D622C47373488F6E5C98E82B9F7FE", "Pillow")
NSLOCTEXT("", "853DDAD141AF7C5BC83E1CA08CB5A0D3", "Shaped of clay and fired in a kiln, jugs are used to store liquids and perishable foodstuff.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "B9C571734492A6D1B06ED18E33555A0F", "For those who can afford to work in iron, metal pots are the fastest way to boil water for cooking, bathing and pouring onto the heads of enemies.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E00620CC42A639894042E18F6943AC7F", "A metal vessel for preparing food")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "B7FD1A8D4CB4F64AB5B3329B7E91B86A", "Popular in Nemedia and Aquilonia, the mortaria are shallow bowl used for mixing, beating and pounding food.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "92172E68419EAB1EE0A9B8875AD1A5D8", "While they vary from culture to culture, iron pans are generally used for cooking in the hot ashes of a fire or on warmed stones.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "78221630451517799E9C98955CF832D3", "Used for long term storage or long haul transportation of goods, the sturdy barrel can be found in wagons, storehouses and taprooms.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "A0C678A840BB7FFC7BA756ABFC66E1F1", "<span style="italic">When a candle was relighted, most of the guests had gone out by doors and broken windows, and the rest huddled behind stacks of wine kegs and under tables.</>
Tower of the Elephant

Wine is the most commonly available alcoholic drink in the Hyborian age. Even the poorest of peasants can get their hands on cheap wine and noblemen guzzle the refined wines of Poitain by the keg.
This small keg bears no maker?s mark to give away its vintage, but if it isn?t vinegar, somebody will drink it.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "84989ACF48427BACA634E88B5C2A9B30", "<span style="italic">He remembered great horns of foaming ale, jacks of sparkling wine gulped carelessly or spilled on the tavern floor.</>
A Witch Shall be Born

Ale is the choice drink of fighting men, especially in taverns where the wine is sour. Served in foaming tankards from large oaken kegs, ale is usually served at room temperature and has a rich fruit flavor.
This keg bears no specific maker?s mark, but that won?t stop anybody from drinking it")
NSLOCTEXT("", "054B0A544F7E9A17DDBD218520B91E70", "This simple shelf can be placed against almost any wall and used to display small objects.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "44D1CB554CD5CC57D950ACBF14A75D3A", "Moth eaten and ragged, this flag is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "CE2B6CA542DD0255CEC76FB1DEAC18D5", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "52A4F6124529C2E0873EBE94E5C71622", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "92E935944A01A589B3CD8AAA7BC9F022", "Woven of coarse fibers, this banner is decorated with common patterns that are found in taverns and temples the length of Stygia.\nStygian ornamentation tends to reflect their cultural worship for the Set and his pantheon.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "4BF02C224F7361F2E138ABA2B7558BCD", "A bronze gong mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "60B25E784693874AE87449998D1265F6", "<span style="italic">Startingly, shockingly in the slumberous stillness, there had boomed the deep strident clangor of a great gong!</>
Jewels of Gwahlur
The clamor of gongs ringing from the temples of a hundred different deities rouses the common folk of Hyboria from sleep each morning. 
Gongs are used mainly for ceremony in temples while noblemen use gongs to summon servants to obey their whims.
It is rumored that in far Khitai, gongs are used to summon the spirits of the ancestors, or drive them forth into the night.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "69C238EF4A6925AA80663084F374E194", "A huge warhorn mounted on a wooden frame")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "0B564E9C4C1D8815A29C818034AB4C7A", "<span style="italic">So she lay without conscious thought or motion, while outside the drums bellowed, the horns clamored, and barbaric voices lifted hideous chants, keeping time to naked feet slapping the hard earth and open palms smiting one another softly.</>
The Vale of Lost Women
The call to battle is often sounded on small horns carried by cavalry. During a battle these horns are used to communicate and rally the troops.
This horn however, is enormous, and can only be used with defence in mind. The one who winds this horn is sending an intimidating message to their enemies I am here, come and take me if you can.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "A478051F4D892A26B6F0218B86DE7548", "Wind chimes crafted of human bones")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "4CB6A44A4AFB7558D590E8A6FC9E4A60", "The cannibal tribes of Darfar have developed a unique mechanism to warn them against the sandstorms that occasionally sweep through their lands. These wind chimes, made from the bones of humans, begin to chime when the wind picks up. If a sandstorm is coming, the noise of the chimes becomes impossible to ignore.\nWhen the wind moves sluggishly through the Darfari camps, however, the chimes create an eerie, ghostly music. Perhaps this unsettling tune contributes to the unsettling reputation of the Darfari.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "0548700E42953B5F3C5F7F9CA0A00051", "A wooden box for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "937DC7A84F13CB78D980CD976B3E5770", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this box is made from simple materials. It can be locked against strangers, but a determined thief will be able to smash it open and take what they please.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "44165B6A4619895B735805A21F864E31", "A large chest for storing items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "DDE9E23E471C8931F5D4F886B63EB003", "Somewhere to place excess items and materials, this chest is made from sturdy materials. It can be locked against strangers, and all but the most determined thief will be deterred. No system is perfect, however.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "B200B7DF4D06BBA33044A88B190EB866", "A vault for storing valuable items")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "9BD33C5B4A1E3B8B9B4F9B9215492D42", "This vault, made from steel and iron, represents the most secure location to store excess items and materials. Breaking into this vault will require a heroic effort.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "D52A06ED4705413FCACD828D732367FB", "A ceramic vase of explosive powder")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "22EF37784BD66443717B99BE659A09B0", "Originally created in Khitai for use in fireworks, enterprising warriors and merchants soon saw the value of using this explosive powder in warfare.\nThe jars are prepared, filled with the powder and carefully sealed against the air. The very touch of air is enough to ignite the powder yet each jar comes with a fuse that can be lit for a delayed detonation.\n")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "45E6227542CAA1104E59E2870CEEF6F0", "An iron trap for capturing medium sized animals")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "A57B101648C8375D0ED36D938E0B5B22", "<span style="italic"> The jaws of an iron trap had closed on his leg, with teeth that sank deep and held. Only the ridged muscles of his calf saved the bone from being splintered.</>
Red Nails
These traps were originally conceived by noblemen in Zingara to prevent human poachers from trespassing on their estate. The effectiveness of the traps was legendary and it wasn?t very long until the traps were being used by hunters across the western kingdoms to capture animals.
When the jaws close on the hapless creature, it is stuck fast, unable to move until it is freed from the trap. Iron and steel traps are in special demand due to the ability to reuse them almost immediately.
This trap is only effective on medium sized animals and humanoids.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "91D3691741FAF8F19F9FBBBFAD453C1D", "A pressure sensitive floor panel that releases sharpened spikes")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "D4DEB7444DA70E6986F73EA0A383F05B", "<span style="italic"> Not the gray lotus, this time, but something just as effective. Nearly every chamber in my house is a trap.</>
Rogues in the House
Honest people defend their homes with stout walls and strength of arms. But devious people know that once a wall is breached, their enemy will be off guard. There are many traps that can be concealed within the walls and floor of a keep and thieves and conquerors alike would do well to keep their wits about them.
Nabonidus, the Red Priest, is rumoured to have filled his mansion with traps to kill the assassins and thieves which came to rob him of life and loot respectively. Ultimately they proved ineffective, as he was found murdered in his own mansion one morning, just inches from the trigger to one of his own traps.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "2287C9614043D3350ECB6DB49CF2B2E8", "A wooden trap for capturing small animals")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "88045DB74BCFCD46606151B6C0C92B94", "This small trap is useful for capturing game and other small animals. It is not strong enough to keep anything larger than a rabbit pinned for very long.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "BF3445924C67DFDC3D4CB9ACE79A63AB", "A ceiling trap that causes blindness ")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "1FD3FB214C6581F901F2E68F2A05CCB1", "<span style="italic"> In the middle of the ceiling hung a cluster of gold buds; these had opened like the petals of a great carven rose, and from them billowed a gray mist that swiftly filled the chamber. Instantly the scene changed from one of hysteria to one of madness and horror. The trapped men began to stagger; they ran in drunken circles. Froth dripped from their lips, which twisted as in awful laughter. Raging, they fell upon one another with daggers and teeth, slashing, tearing, slaying in a holocaust of madness.</>
Rogues in the House
The pollen of the gray lotus is known to cause madness among men and the original version of this trap, developed by Nabonidus the Red Priest, takes full advantage of that.
The gray lotus grows only in the Swamps of the Dead beyond Khitai, so in this version of the trap, the lotus pollen is replaced with Tomb dust which can be obtained in the Unnamed City.
The trap is simple, a trigger in the floor which opens bags of the dust hidden in the ceiling.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "3B5763D4439EBEF7C0ED19BC0FF0EB97", "A shrine to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "35FEA0654EDD3CC184B82D9F2C6CBB99", "<span style="italic">Ships did not put unasked into this port, where dusky sorcerers wove awful spells in the murk of sacrificial smoke mounting eternally from blood-stained altars where naked women screamed, and where Set, the Old Serpent, arch-demon of the Hyborians but god of the Stygians, was said to writhe his shining coils among his worshippers.</>
The Hour of the Dragon

Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine shrine will not remain so for long. 
The hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.
Altars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "0E760DED484BCCF7D1119A83AD19B1B9", "An altar to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "7C9CD5514ED4643ADCAC2C8493A5BC8A", "Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine altar will not remain so for long. \nThe hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.\nAltars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "21D51F524B87B1FB40DF799E8663FC35", "An altar to Set, the Old Serpent")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "97FA3ABF4A3446C440E02B946C10CF8B", "Created as a focal point for the worship of Set, this pristine altar will not remain so for long. \nThe hunger of Set requires human sacrifice and the altars of Set regularly run with blood.\nAltars can also be used to perform rituals of creation - placing certain items on the altar can invoke the blessings of the gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "AB79048443FBE0513B2071A5969E3FEB", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "8978AF564D0998386DB62AA59945A444", "<span style="italic">Somewhere near by had been the pit, dark and awful, wherein screaming victims were fed to a nameless amorphic monstrosity which came up out of a deeper, more hellish cavern.</>
Black Colossus

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 
When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.
It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "11C2ABEB4D709EF5D4628796C538F973", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "70B7931347CE520EAFA6A2A38816BC86", "<span style="italic">At the edge of the desert, beyond the houses, there is a clump of palm trees, and within that grove there is a pit. And within that pit have been found human bones, charred and blackened. Not once, but many times!</>
Shdows in Zamboula

The altars of Yog are crude sacrifice pits, lined with spikes and stones. Victims are hauled up to a rough stone platform and then uncerimonously booted into the pit. 
When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.
It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "722835F54DDA8D9F2A2756AF0756950C", "A sacrifice pit made for the glory of Yog")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "3CBC8DD34CAF2486352763B24E5401CA", "<span style="italic">He understood now the mystery of the strangers who had disappeared from the house of Aram Baksh; the riddle of the black drum thrumming out there beyond the palm groves, and of that pit of charred bones -- that pit where strange meat might be roasted under the stars, while black beasts squatted about to glut a hideous hunger.</>
Shdows in Zamboula

When the victim has finished shrieking, the worshippers of Yog gather and partake of the purified flesh.
It is said that the blessing of Yog falls upon anything within the pit. It is not uncommon to meet Yoggites who have smeared themselves with ashes from their sacrifice pits and decorated themselves with the bones of their victims.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "38F4CDED4B967B666AA72D87C01F244D", "A holy shrine dedicated to the worship of Mitra")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "7B4B4B5D429AC01A255484A9927B556D", "Considered a good god, Mitra is worshipped throughout the Hyborian kings, replacing the worship of Bori from which those primitive tribes took their name.\nMitra\'s symbol is that of the phoenix, but when he is depicted it is in the form of a well built, bearded man. He abhors the bloody rituals of other religions and prefers for his followers to perform dignified, purification rituals.\nMitra\'s priests preach a monotheistic doctrine and as such their followers tend to persecute the members of other nearby religions. Due to this tendency, Chapels to Mitra cannot be built within a very long range of shrines to other gods.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FE9EC822432CFAD5C1A2B3A6C221ACAB", "A statue in the image of Mitra that pours forth water")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "7CDC769342655DBE9787B38FAC2D4DD2", "Through the mysteries of Mitra it is possible to call water to well forth eternally. This affirmation of Mitra\'s power is marred somewhat by those who claim that the worshippers of Mitra only build these over pre-existing streams.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "FA02C9874E7A40E3655C03923DAD5658", "A statue in the image of Mitra that radiates holy light")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "433E6A194E9AD6696ACEED8567ABEBEB", "It is said that the lights on these statues will burn eternally as long as Mitra has a single faithful follower. It can be argued, of course, that a single faithful follower of Mitra would also keep the light burning to perpetuate the mysteries of Mitra and therefore create a paradox which has theologians everywhere going to sleep each night with a sore head.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "A345DC3D4812A1698D3BBEA764B8CDC2", "A small campfire for cooking and keeping warm")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "5777DCED456EC92E5414EDA6C2237651", "<span style="italic">'Lie here.' He indicated a clean-swept space close to a small flickering fire. He saw no incongruity in a princess lying down on the naked ground beside a campfire, wrapped in a warrior's cloak.</>
Black Colossus

The campfire is an adventurers best friend when the nights turn cold and the darkness presses in all around.
Made from simple branches and twigs, the campfire is an excellent source of light and heat.
Campfires can be used to cook meat which is important given the number of parasites that infect the wild animals of the Exiled Lands. Better to eat some burned meat, than be poisoned for days.
With the light of a campfire, however, comes visibility. Wary travelers would do well to hide their fires, lest they be ambushed in the night by men with unsavory intentions.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "ECCE56E24AACEAB4F0CC2D8A21A0A613", "<span style=\"italic\">They camped that night on the northern slopes of those hills, and hook-nosed, fiery-eyed men of the hill tribes came in scores to squat about the fires and repeat news that had come up out of the mysterious desert. </>- Black Colossus\nBuilt of large pieces of wood, the bonfire is a blazing beacon in the night. Bonfires give off more light and heat tahn their lesser relative, the campfire, which can be an advantage if the priority is to remain warm, or a disadvantage if the priority is to remain hidden.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "574705894F0726D276F51BBE76DC6715", "A furnace for smelting metals and stone")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "542E6CFD4E4738626BEB778C829A7C15", "<span style=\"italic\">Logs flamed in the wide fireplace, for there was a frosty edge to the air, and a great meat pasty in a stone platter stood smoking on a broad mahogany board.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\nDesigned to heat ore to incredibly high temperatures in order to extract pure metals, furnaces require fuels such as coal or wood and ores for processing and catalysts such as Steelfire for strengthening. Intense heat can also be used to harden certain types of stone and a furnace can be used in conjunction with other concoctions to create hardened stone bricks.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "E273E5494A0CB794EB002581789B25DA", "<span style="italic">On the ivory throne-seat Tascela lolled. Bronze bowls of incense rolled their spirals about her; the wisps of smoke curled about her naked limbs like caressing fingers.</> - Red Nails
The humble cauldron is conventionally used by chefs to create meals. However, the versatility of the cauldorn means that it is also sought after by alchemists and sorcerers who concoct strange experiments.
Smelting catalysts such as Steelfire, can only be created by an alchemist who knows the particular combination of ingredients.
This particular type of cauldron was first used commonly in Vendhya.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E10E02804011B177D55FD7B85ADF03C4", "A tannery for processing hides into leather")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "6E07E30549512CFC4919C6AAD2329A56", "<span style=\"italic\">They were young men, but hard and sinewy, with a bearing that comes only to men rendered desperate by adversity. They were clad in mail shirts and worn leather; swords hung at their girdles.</> - A Witch Shall be Born\nThe stench of the tannery is easily identifiable in the major cities of the world and tanners are often relegated to the outskirts of cities or villages, preferably downstream. \nBark is the most common form of tannin used to convert hide into leather. During the process it breaks down into Tar, which is a useful catalyst for alchemists.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "6E806922452A362A9AE220B8C92E2561", "A bench covered in tools for crafting armor")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "5AAFDD6548FAD5F448DC208DF1AE8BF4", "<span style=\"italic\">With the firelight glinting from his blue steel armor, he seemed like an image of steel - dynamic power for the moment quiescent; not resting, but motionless for the instant, awaiting the signal to plunge again into terrific action.</> - Black Colossus\nCreating armor, particularly metal armor, requires a large number of exotic tools. This armormaking bench can be used to create anything from the lightest leather armor to hardened steel armor. Provided that the raw materials are available, of course.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E7E8FAB84855A70FDA30418637D0A073", "A bench covered in tools for shaping metal")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "F1C2CFDF43977D124514D3B27099FF88", "<span style=\"italic\">That is to say, they had learned to work crudely in copper and tin, which were found scantily in their country, and for which latter metal they raided into the mountains of Zingara, or traded hides, whale\'s teeth, walrus tusks and such few things as savages have to trade.</>- The Hyborian Age\nSmithing is a well-known and oft-used profession in the Hyborian kingdoms. In the larger cities and towns, smiths are forced to join guilds that offer them a certain amount of political protection, while enforcing a rigorous set of standards of work and tools.\nThis bench contains many of the tools that smiths need, but in the Exiled Lands, there are no standards to be enforced.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "20C5874641A8C2DA56EB968FA4A906F6", "A bench covered in tools for carpentry")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "8EADA48D417DF9C165ACA89E80A055D5", "<span style=\"italic\">\"Our merciful sovereign offers you one more chance, Countess,\" said the tallest of the three, and he spoke Aquilonian without an accent. \"He bids me say that if you soften your proud, rebellious spirit, he will still open his arms to you. If not-\" he gestured toward a grim wooden block in the center of the cell. It was blackly stained, and showed many deep nicks as if a keen edge, cutting through some yielding substance, had sunk into the wood.</> - The Hour of the Dragon\nThe ability to work wood is a useful skill for anybody interested in creating buildings and furniture. This bench is covered with all of the implements that one needs to create anything from houses to chairs.")
NSLOCTEXT("", "CCAB83954069B9567364C2900F1ADBD3", "Lashing Post (1 slot)")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "0E72A93A4514EA6B17330C8DB18C67C0", "A wheel that strengthens the body as it breaks the mind")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "282BAD16406CB6D6BA20EDB1C42D0C1F", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not care anymore. Life and death... the same.</> - Conan the Barbarian \nThis wheel is based on a design that originally comes from the mountains and valleys of Vanaheim. It is unclear whether it serves any purpose other than to keep prisoners passive and exhausted until they can be used for more productive tasks.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "1B46C949433BA43ACB45CE9536B8F700", "A square foundation piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "AC3DBEA248240748CD4C64A32D5A50B8", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting sandstone buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "20947E264D4D2441CC3FAD87A7A577A0", "A square wall piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "289C56F648595651ECCC0FA67C5B9A4C", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "4A7E336D4211332325430CB959C51525", "A square ceiling piece made of sandstone")
column4:
NSLOCTEXT("", "F7DEFB1043FB3F74CC46F7A7ADD7A831", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "0CFC0FC945A7C3E744BE229A1ED74C2F", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "9BBD874C416A74D66CA275B318543A03", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "56F02C4F409FA3E7CB4987BF53FD4911", "A wedge shaped piece of sandstone ")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "BEDB2DDD45D4076FB3D23C82864C0C16", "Wedge shaped building pieces allow greater flexibility in the shapes available to builders.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "AA324C53416CCA66847CAEBB23438E56", "A sandstone wall with space for a window")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "78352CDE413262597294869799185FF9", "Windows provide great vantage points for archers without forcing them to leave the safety of stout walls.\nCobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.\nDespite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "DD53A5EE41A282A417CBB7BA7429664B", "Created from the most basic materials available in the Exiled Lands, this simple wooden door offers access to friends and denies it to foes.\nThe wood has aged in the desert sun and will not be strong enough to hold out determined foes, but it will keep the weather outside.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "B39E253E4C9AFF7B41735D897BAFB38C", "Cobbled together from ill-fitting stones buttressed by flimsy branches scavenged from the environment, this is barely a step above rubble.
Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "E65FB34C43260E58C2E87F8773139606", "A fence piece made of sandstone")
column4:

This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. 
Despite its appearance, it will provide some protection from the elements and the predators that roam the Exiled Lands. Determined foes, however, will find it no barrier.
")

NSLOCTEXT("", "96C3C68547244A8C7FBFC0960B8BC67B", "Foundations should be the starting point for almost any structure. They provide stability to anything built atop them and prevent the growth of plants beneath them.
Placing a foundation is a significant act in the Exiled Lands. Once a foundation is placed by a clan or individual, that land is considered their territory. Nobody else may build in the immediate area, unless the foundation is destroyed.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

NSLOCTEXT("", "6B402D6741EC75F6DE130F982F3F092E", "Walls are a comfort for the timid, a strength to the strategist and a trap for the unwary.
A barrier against the savage world, walls can be built as high as the stability of the foundations will allow. The strength of the materials used in their construction will determine how long they stay up.
Just remember to add a door.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

NSLOCTEXT("", "22F8DF9648C8854D25FFBF9458A7CDFA", "It is said that nobody is truly home until they have a roof over their head. Across the civilizations of Hyboria, rooves are made from a diverse number of materials ? from clay-fired tiles warmed in the kilns of Agarapar to the roughly thatched rooves of the Nordheimers. 
In the Exiled Lands, however, materials are limited. Something to keep the sandstorms at bay and the bat demons from swooping down and snatching people while they sleep is probably good enough.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

NSLOCTEXT("", "DAB8930B4683EB2C5ED5998DCD95A003", "Every structure that has ever fallen to an enemy has been breached somewhere. And the breach point, more often than not, is the door.
A door is only as strong as the place where it is anchored and many a would-be warlord has come to grief when their solidly constructed door was torn off at the anchor point.
The difference between a king and a pauper might just be the entrance to his kingdom.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

NSLOCTEXT("", "38F5E53E4D5488A26756FBAC0A4AB36F", "Any warrior with even a little battle hardening will agree that the safest ground to defend is the high ground. And if there is no high ground to defend, make it yourself.
Stairs are a necessity once buildings grow beyond a certain size. They provide points of natural defence and easy access to higher floors and rooftops (which make excellent archery platforms). Their only weakness is the material upon which they are built ? if the high ground is brought crashing down then it no longer serves a tactical purpose.
Built of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.
")

column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "D332BD10405BA743E9DD659958D5151F", "Wedges are used to expand the possibilities of a building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "52073C344F7248A0A59BABA2C038139A", "This is a wall with some stones removed to create space for a window. Useful for letting in natural light and keeping an eye on the surroundings.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "A4AE45E74092F724208765B8350E6F52", "Shaped wooden planks reinforced with iron bands are used to create this solid door. While providing access, this door also provides significant protection against intruders.")

NSLOCTEXT("", "28EE8BDF4609D5E15B3DCD82DD73D570", "Pillars offer stability to tall structures, allowing height to become a significant factor in building. Be aware, however, that pillars also offer a unique weak point for enemies to attack.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "B26F65B1446834E655CDFAB3A9940871", "This low fence is not designed to keep enemies out, but rather to provide defensive archers with a measure of cover between shots. \nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "11915B914881903D391944A19710F83D", "Wedge foundations allow unique shapes to be created when building.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "D19EA5414A65BBFA41E9BA8AEA2D8441", "Sloped rooves are practical in sandstorms as the loose debris simply runs from the roof rather than accumulating.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.\n")

NSLOCTEXT("", "58E01FBE46E3BE3C71E620AEF0EBBD35", "The best battle, as they say, is the one you never have to fight. With formidable enough gates, the enemies will think twice about attacking any fortress. Not simply because the scale of the gates has them concerned about getting inside, but because large gates imply large inhabitants and armies get nervous when they think they might be outnumbered.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column3: NSLOCTEXT("", "9C5EAE9649F7FF126B11989974248770", "Sturdy doors to keep enemies at bay")
column4: NSLOCTEXT("", "6321458E4184463E8AE485BB057127B9", "These large doors are designed to allow access for large groups of people in and out of safe areas. Raiders and bandits make walls a must have in the Exiled Lands and the protection afforded by gates such as these should not be taken for granted.\nBuilt of close fitting bricks of cut Stonebrick, reinforced by wooden slats that have been shaped to fit, this will provide a safe haven from the weather and strong front to any foes who come knocking.")

column4:
